<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE5FE6B48A755DEFE0CFB66" pageId="427" pageNumber="428" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FE5FE6B48A755DEFF64FB82" blockId="427.[151,1436,754,1355]" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE5FE6B48A755DEFE30FCFB" bold="true" box="[151,405,754,779]" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 1.8–2.0 mm. Head brown, except mandible testaceous; antenna testaceous; mesosoma and metasoma brown; legs yellow. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 2:2:4:4:3.8:3.5:3.5:3.3:3.3:4.3; antennal segment 3 more than three times as long as broad (4:1.2). Head shiny, granulated; frontal line incomplete, only shortly present in front of anterior ocellus; occipital carina absent; temple distinct; POL = 9; OL = 4; OOL = 6; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli about as long as OL. Palpal formula 5/2. Scutum dull, granulated. Notauli complete, posteriorly separated, very close, almost joint. Scutellum with anterior half granulated and posterior half unsculptured. Metanotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Propodeum with dorsal surface shiny, smooth, unsculptured; posterior surface dull, reticulate rugose, without longitudinal or transverse keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein longer than proximal part (11.5:4.5). Dorsal process of paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B4ABA531AFCA2FBBE" box="[650,775,1078,1102]" captionStart="PLATE 131" captionStartId="418.[151,233,1874,1897]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,256,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-111@418.[151,1436,243,1817]" captionTargetPageId="418" captionText="PLATE 131. A–D. Male genitalia. E,G, I. Mesosoma. F, H, J.Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus rufoniger from China. B, I, J. G. superbus (from Olmi 1987c). C. G. asiaticus from Japan. D. G. leurosipropodeus, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). E, F. G. schenklingi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). G, H. G. sitae (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.18 mm for B, 0.15 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.21 mm for F, 0.34 mm for H, and 0.32 mm for J." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278836" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278836/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 131D</figureCitation>
) long and slender, with distal apex pointed. Tibial spurs 1/ 1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FE5FE6B48F75353FE0CFB66" blockId="427.[151,1436,754,1355]" box="[199,425,1150,1175]" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">
